author: leosimons
msg: Bulk update of the libb contribution to incorporate changes made to libb within
Joost while libb was being set up, as previously discussed on the triplesoup development mailing list. Normal CCLA/CLA terms apply. Code by Andrea M.
The main changes are
* addition of a standard GNU automake/autoconf/etc build system
* addition of a new journalling engine
* addition of an rdf2b tool to ingest RDF data into B
* some miscelleneous bug fixes
* cleanup of the redland patch
The change log from Joost's SVN repository:
r68326: B - Makefile.am with the redland's patch
r62466: B - makefile.am about utils
r62462: B - storage - rdf2b - it parses a RDF document and puts it into a B storage
r56872: B - 2 checks added
r56870: B - md5 and svn release in the tarball
r55218: B - autogen script changed
r55217: B - This export script creates the tarball from this SVN
r55200: B - tarball autocreating
r55193: B - tarball - other 3 files
r55179: B - directory with documentation, configure.ac, makefile.ams and other files for autotools. This staff creates the tarball
r55174: B - deleting procedure fixed
r54774: B - b_el_t functions in a separated file
r54768: B - iterator with compare triple fixed
r54574: B - a best code, some check added, other stuff
r54489: B - storage with journaling engine.
